node.title: One killed, one injured in hit and run in Melbourne's south-east
node.description: Police say the driver of a red Holden fled on foot after the vehicle hit several pedestrians at Carrum Downs, in Melbourne's south-east.
node.content: ["Police are investigating a hit and run in Melbourne's south-east that has left one person dead and another with life-threatening injuries.", "Detectives said a red Holden struck a number of people near the intersection of Hall Road and Lats Avenue at Carrum Downs around 7:15am.", "One person died at the scene and a second person was flown to hospital.", "Police said the driver of the vehicle initially fled on foot and was last seen getting into a black Hyundai SUV, which then travelled east on Ballarto Road.", "Police said the driver was Caucasian in appearance and aged in his 30s.", "Anyone who witnessed the crash or has dashcam footage of the incident has been asked to contact CrimeStoppers on 1800 333 000.", "More to come."]
